in other dream i had too, they would like to take me with them. nevertheless in 2007 i left haiti to come to live alone in dominican republic and to study medical science; and in 2010, 11 years later the first events that i lived in haiti, an alien had come to my apartment at 1:00 am. he was outside of the window with his arm inside of the bathroom. when i saw him he hid a part of his face but his arm was stayed in. i stared at him without fear. he looked a good one. it seems he wanted me to shake hands with him cause his arm was still staying extended till he pulled it out. a few seconds after he left mysteriously. but he was exactly that one i used to see in my dreams before and that i drew in the paper. so after he left i was a little scared. i couldn't even turn off the light to sleep! i couldn't believe that i came to see an alien! i felt so strange! i asked myself who am i to get visited by an alien? so what he wanted from me? in 2014, i had another dream, "i saw men in black in limousine came to my house and look for me. i tried to get away from them and they caught me anyway then they said to me: "you cannot escape from us; you got something inside of you who belongs to us, you are one of us". and then they disappeared". when i woke up on that morning the palm of my right hand was all green color like a leaf of a tree. i washed my hands, nothing! so scared of what was happening to me! i went to some friend's house to show my hand. they couldn't help then worried. three hours after my right hand was normal without i realized it. the dreams say the truth sometimes. i can't understand this phenomenon! can i please have any explications in that case? thank you!

content.detailedDescription: Each evening between 10/5/15 and 10/7/15 i was driving home from work and was within a half mile of my house when i observed two white rectangular objects spaced some distance apart.  they were both at the same altitude approximately 25 degrees above the eastern horizon.  they caught my attention because even though it was cloudy each night they were prominent objects.  i originally thought they were airplanes or blimps, but they did not have their characteristic shape after longer observation.  they did not move during the time that i observed them and they appeared to be in the same location each evening.   i was very nervous by their sighting and have not seen any local news indicating they were easy explained by a human made object.  i only saw them when i was high enough to see over the treeline.
content.summary: Two white rectangular stationary objects hovering in evening sky

content.summary: Very bright starlike brightness no noticeable strobes or aircraft identifiers

content.detailedDescription: I came home from concert. for some reason, as i never do this and that is what is strange to me is that i did so immediately when i closed my garage for some odd prompting, i stood there on the street and stared at the stars (actually a clear night!) just looking for about a minute.  not moving, just standing there. all of a sudden, i saw one "star"appear, turn very bright like venus and perhaps a slight blue tint, then disappear. it was visible for about 3 seconds. about two minutes later it appeared again, very bright like before, then disappeared. then i saw a very fast "shooting star" in the same area of the sky but not exactly the same area, move northeast and disappear. i don't think it was a shooting star, though. then the bright "star" light appeared again, very bright, then disappeared. it seemed to be slowly moving due east by it's third appearance. i didn't see it again.It only was visible for about three seconds for each time. **i went inside my house and googled this. many people report seeing a very bright star and disappear. some are on video (you tube.) i'm not the only one who has seen this. people from all across the world have been reporting this on forums and you tube.**
content.summary: Stargazing. star-like glow appeared from no where, bright bluish-white glow bigger than venus, 3 seconds, then disappeared. occurred three times.

content.detailedDescription: The objects were first noticed by our grandson out the bedroom window facing west. at about 8:15 pm we went outside and observed a cluster of four lights hovering in the sky.  approximate distance appeared to be about 5 miles.  the lights appeared out of nowhere in the western sky.  we thought at first they were helicopters.  one by one they began to move to the north and then turn toward the south.  they each passed directly overhead with a minimum of noise.  this is when we knew they were not helicopters or military aircraft.  they didn't generate enough noise to be either.  each had flashing lights...Blue/green, white and red. as one would leave the cluster to begin the move to the north, another light would appear to the left of the cluster and join the line of objects.  this was repeated until 10 to 15 objects had appeared and moved north and then south. the entire event took place over the span of about an hour.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Cluster of lights in western sky. slow movement to west and then south.

content.detailedDescription:
While heading west/northwest on i-80, approximately 30 miles east of north platt, ne, at 7:20 pm on october 5, 2015, we observed a brilliant stationary light 30 degrees above the horizon approximately 45 degrees left of our course on the interstate.  the sun had just set when the object appeared.  we observed that it was a spherical light in a stationary position for five minutes.  it was far brighter than two airplanes that were flying overhead on an easterly path at almost the same time that we saw the object.  there were no stars visible in the sky, as this was just at sunset and the sky was still very bright.  the object was larger than any star or planet that we had seen in the night sky on the previous night.  we pulled off the highway to observe the object, and retrieved our binoculars.  while i was retrieving the glasses, my wife noted that the object changed shape, increasing in size, elongating and seeming to develop a veil-like shape, so that it resembled a filmy rectangle.  the color was yellow-white.  with the field glasses, i observed the object rise in a straight line at a rapid velocity, and change from a pulsating/rotating white/yellow to bright orange, as it decreased in size.
while i was observing this, the object vanished. it didn't disappear into the distance - it simply vanished, like a switch had been flipped.  the entire event lasted approximately 10 minutes.  we waited for a couple of minutes in wonder and tried to assess what we had seen, and comparing the relative size to the planes we had seen that had flown on eastward.  this object was  much larger than those planes had been.  we drove on, and saw nothing more...
content.summary: Pulsating light near north platt, nebraska
